| Feature               | Logic-1 (Table-Driven AI) | Logic-2 (Rule-Based AI) |
|-----------------------|--------------------------|--------------------------|
| AI Type               | Table-Driven              | Rule-Based               |
| Decision Method       | Lookup Table              | Strategy Rules           |
| Knowledge Storage     | Precomputed Move Table    | No Stored Table          |
| Memory Usage          | High                      | Low                      |
| Flexibility           | Low                       | High                     |
| Scalability           | Poor                      | Better                   |
| Intelligence Type     | Stored Knowledge          | Reasoning-Based          |
| Human-like Thinking   | No                        | Yes                      |
| Real-Time Decision    | No                        | Yes                      |
| Adaptability          | Fixed                     | Dynamic                  |
| Computation During Play | None                    | Yes (Rule Evaluation)    |
| Suitability for Large Games | Not Suitable        | More Suitable            |

Logic-1 is knowledge-intensive, whereas Logic-2 is reasoning-intensive.
